cs.RO, cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.HC 

Reasoning: 
1. cs.RO (Robotics): The paper focuses on robotic surgery and proposes a method to obtain haptic feedback using visual cues. 
2. cs.CV (Computer Vision): The proposed method uses deep learning to infer forces from endoscopic video, which falls under the domain of computer vision. 
3. cs.LG (Machine Learning): The paper employs deep learning to predict surgical forces, which falls under the domain of machine learning. 
4. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence): The proposed method involves the use of artificial intelligence techniques to infer forces from video. 
5. cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction): The paper discusses the limitations of obtaining haptic feedback in robotic surgery and proposes a low-cost and accurate alternative, which falls under the domain of human-computer interaction.
